{"model": "Qwen 2.5 Coder 32B Instruct", "runtime": "mlx", "prompt_name": "logic_ages__t3_cot", "prompt_tokens": 94, "generation_tokens": 304, "prompt_tps": 369.7184829623358, "generation_tps": 24.167414196966355, "peak_memory_gb": 18.713504464, "wall_time_sec": 12.893987832998391, "output": "Let's denote Bob's current age as \\( B \\) and Alice's current age as \\( A \\).\n\nFrom the problem, we know two things:\n1. Alice is twice as old as Bob, so \\( A = 2B \\).\n2. In 10 years, Alice will be 1.5 times as old as Bob, so \\( A + 10 = 1.5(B + 10) \\).\n\nFirst, substitute the expression for \\( A \\) from the first equation into the second equation:\n\\[ 2B + 10 = 1.5(B + 10) \\]\n\nNext, distribute the 1.5 on the right side:\n\\[ 2B + 10 = 1.5B + 15 \\]\n\nNow, subtract \\( 1.5B \\) from both sides to get all the \\( B \\) terms on one side:\n\\[ 2B - 1.5B + 10 = 15 \\]\n\\[ 0.5B + 10 = 15 \\]\n\nSubtract 10 from both sides:\n\\[ 0.5B = 5 \\]\n\nFinally, divide both sides by 0.5 to solve for \\( B \\):\n\\[ B = \\frac{5}{0.5} \\]\n\\[ B = 10 \\]\n\nSo, Bob is currently 10 years old.\n\nANSWER: 10", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "a33ec0efd7f9", "quant": "4bit"}
